4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LAWS RELATED TO THE MANAGEMENT OF GRAY
5 WOLVES; REQUIRING THE FISH AND WILDLIFE COMMISSION TO APPLY DIFFERENT TECHNIQUES
6 FOR THE MANAGEMENT OF GRAY WOLVES; ALLOWING THE USE OF THERMAL AND INFRARED
7 SCOPES FOR GRAY WOLF MANAGEMENT; AMENDING SECTION 87-1-901, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN
8 IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 Section 1. Section 87-1-901, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "87-1-901. Gray wolf management -- rulemaking -- reporting. (1) Except as provided in subsection
14 (3), the commission shall establish by rule hunting and trapping seasons for wolves with the intent to reduce the
15 wolf population in this state to a sustainable level, but not less than the number of wolves necessary to support
16 at least 15 breeding pairs. Trapping seasons must allow for the use of snares by the holder of a trapping
17 license.
18 (2) For game management purposes, the commission may shall apply different management
19 techniques depending on the conditions in each administrative region, with the most liberal harvest regulations
20 applied in regions with the greatest number of wolves. In doing so, the commission may shall authorize:
21 (a) the issuance of more than one Class E-1 or Class E-2 wolf hunting license to an applicant;
22 (b) the trapping or snaring of more than one wolf by the holder of a trapping license;
23 (c) the harvest of an unlimited number of wolves by the holder of a single wolf hunting or wolf
24 trapping license;
25 (d) during the wolf trapping season, the use of bait while hunting or trapping wolves as long as no
26 trap or snare trap is set within 30 feet of exposed bait visible from above; and
27 (e) the hunting of wolves on private lands outside of daylight hours with the use of artificial light, or
28 night vision scopes, infrared scopes, or thermal imagery scopes.
